&lt;p&gt;A combinatorial proof shows that $A$ and $B$ are the same thing by showing that they are solutions to the &lt;strong&gt;same counting problem&lt;/strong&gt;. Usually induction or algebraic proofs can also be used to solve these problems, but combinatorial proofs are usually more insightful and elegant.&lt;/p&gt;
